56th Terrace (background), between 56th (left) and 58th Street (right). Maspeth Ave. (foreground) makes a right angle turn in the background intersecting with Maurice Ave. and 58th Street. The old location of the buildings in the background was on the north side of the Road to Town Landing between Maspeth Creek and Betts Ave. The Clinton Park Hotel (in center of view) was demolished in September 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

1922.
title: Queens: 56th Terrace - 56th Street

text:
A general view northeast from 56th Road (along Long Island Railroad tracks) and 56th Street (seen at the left extending toward the north along the side of the Underhill Covert house in the background). The Underhill Covert house is on the north side of 55th Drive between 56th and 58th Streets. Along the line of the fence in the foreground is Fifty-seventh Ave. The New Cavalry Cemetery is in the background.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

January 1924.
title: General view - Queens - 56th Road - 56th Street.
